notes: All 12 Dependabot PRs target transitive dependencies in yarn.lock, not direct dependencies in package.json.
No GitHub Actions or Python Dependabot PRs are open.
The markdown-to-jsx PR (#106) is effectively stale: it upgrades the storybook transitive copy from 7.1.6 to 7.4.0, but the direct production dep is already at 7.7.15.
Many uncovered alerts trace back to storybook (next channel) and tsdx, which are deeply nested dev toolchain dependencies. Upgrading storybook and tsdx would resolve many of these.
The jsonpath alert (#135) is in the production dependency chain (@apideck/wayfinder -> jsonpath) with no known fix version. This is a high-severity issue requiring upstream action.
The single resolutions entry (jest-environment-jsdom) does not conflict with any current Dependabot PRs.
No PRs involve major version bumps, so no breaking change research was needed.
The repo uses storybook 'next' channel and tsdx 0.14.x, both of which pull in webpack 4 and many outdated transitive deps. A storybook + tsdx upgrade would resolve the majority of uncovered alerts.
